edge: The Mummy is a reboot of the Mummy franchise.
In the movie, the ancient tomb of entrapped Egyptian princess Ahmanet is unearthed accidentally by U.S. Army Sergeant Nick Morton.
In the movie, Tom Cruise plays the role of U.S. Army Sergeant Nick Morton, a soldier of fortune.
Ahmanet is an ancient and entrapped Egyptian princess in the movie.
The Mummy's intended goal was to kick-start a modern cinematic universe concept based on the classic Universal Monsters film series, which was named Dark Universe.
The poor box office performance of The Mummy led to the cancellation of the shared universe named Dark Universe.
The Dark Universe name would later be used for a land name at the upcoming Universal Epic Universe featuring similar characters.

After being injured while trying to attack Ahmanet and letting her embrace him as a ruse to steal the dagger and shatter the ruby, Nick stabs himself with the dagger and allows Set to possess him. However, he regains control after remembering both Jenny and Jekyll's words and uses Set's powers to extract Ahmanet's life force, killing her and resurrecting Jenny.
Jenny is captured by Ahmanet and her neck is snapped. Her body remains until Nick returns from his adventure with Chris, at which point he resurrects her.

Guided by Chris's ghost, Nick and Jenny flee into the London Underground with Ahmanet's zombies in pursuit. When Nick is brought to Ahmanet, she reminds him that the dagger could grant him the power to reverse death, but instead of destroying the gem, he stabs himself, allowing Set to possess him.
As Ahmanet is sealed back in her sarcophagus, Jenny and Jekyll wonder whether Nick, now fused with Set, will use his powers for good. Nick returns to the desert and resurrects Chris.
Ahmanet captures Jenny and snaps her neck, but her body remains until Nick resurrects her.
Knowing that Prodigium is coming for him, Nick says goodbye to Jenny and vanishes.
